                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/1331: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 27, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>594. Your 1347, October 18, 6 p.m. In response to the inquiry of the British
                    Embassy, please inform the Embassy orally and informally that you have no
                    comment to make other than to say that you understand that the silver in
                    question is not specifically included in any arrangement now in effect between
                    the American and Chinese Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
